member.name: M:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.IXYMath.AddBoundingPoints(System.Double[]@,System.Single[]@,System.Double,System.Double,System.Double)
member.summary: a) xarray and yarray are the x,y arrays for the PROFILE spectra (caller code should call it only with profile spectra values). b) The length of xarray and yarray should be same otherwise an exception would be thrown. c) If length is less than two points then algorithm would simply return back the arrays(we need minimum two points to add bounding regions). d) We need full xArrays. The XsamplingType for both types of Profile spectra is stepped so xarrays have to be filled and sent to this algorithm . e)minPointSpacing is the smallest possible value of spacing in array. This is NOT the natural point spacing (which the algorithm infers) but simply a value which indicates what is the minimum that is allowed. This should be obtained via a call to MinimumExpectedMsPointSpacing. f) maxMeasured is the maximum value of the MeasuredRange of the spectrum object. This is to ensure that after adding bounding regions we do not exceed the maximum range. g) For TOF profile spectrum the method should be called in the time domain. h) The algorithm would replace the xArray and yArray with ones which have added bounding values. The caller code should handle the BoundedRegions flags and call this code only if BoundedregionFlag is set.
member.param: full array of X -values(equal in length to x-array)
minimum allowed spacing in same data units as xArray.
minimum measured range in same data units as xArray
maximum measured range in same data units as xArray

member.name: P:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.IConsistency.CheckingSuspended
member.summary:
Set or get the flag that allows for temporary suspension of consistency checking. When this is true, HasChanged will return false. When this is false, HasChanged will return the actual value of the changed flag.
Typically used when a caller needs to make many calls to an object, where some of those calls make changes and others would (usually indirectly) invoke MakeConsistent. By bracketing those calls between a calls to suspend and then resume checking, performance may be improved.

member.name: T:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.ILuDecomposition
member.summary:
LU decomposition of a rectangular matrix.
For an m-by-n matrix A with m = n, the LU decomposition is an m-by-n unit lower triangular matrix L, an n-by-n upper triangular matrix U, and a permutation vector piv of length m so that A(piv)=L*U.
The LU decompostion with pivoting always exists, even if the matrix is singular, so the constructor will never fail.

member.name: T:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType
member.summary: Ways in which the x-values of data objects are measured.

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.Unspecified
member.summary: The sampling type is unknown or unspecified

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.Stepped
member.summary: Data are measured at precise, equidistant intervals from a specified initial X value. There are no missing points over the range of the data.
member.remarks: XValue = InitialX + (PointNumber * XSpacing). Points exist for all PointNumbers in the range of the data.

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.SparseStepped
member.summary: Data represent a subset of the values originally measured at precise, equidistant intervals from a specified initial X value.
member.remarks: XValue = InitialX + (PointNumber * XSpacing). Points exist for some, but not necessarily all, of the PointNumbers in the range of the data

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.Discontinuous
member.summary: Data are measured at accurately known X values that may not be (usually are not) equally-spaced.

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.Irregular
member.summary: X values may have some uncertainty and may not be regularly spaced.

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.Continuous
member.summary: Data with some continuous function at precisely known but unequally spaced x values.

member.name: F:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.XSamplingType.BoundedRegions
member.summary: Data have regions of points with equal or slowly varying point spacing. Each such region is bounded by a data point on each side of the region that has Y=0.
member.remarks: Primarily for TOF profile spectra with XUnits = of m/z (Thompsons) or mass (Daltons).

member.name: M:Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.BaseUtilities.GetResourceString(System.String,System.String,Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.StringType,Agilent.MassSpectrometry.DataAnalysis.StringCasing,System.Boolean)
member.summary:
Returns a string from a string table in the assembly from which this function is called. This function is intended for use in which there are several strings that "belong" to the same basic key. The actual key by which the string is sought is based on the basicKey, the keyQualifier (if not null) and the stringType.
The resource strings should be written in Title Case. Their keys should follow the pattern: [Qualifier_]BasicKey (for the normal string or "display name") [Qualifier_]BasicKey_A (for an abbreviated string) [Qualifier_]BasicKey_D (for a longer name or "description")
If there is more than one resource associated with that assembly, this will try to find the string in each resource in turn, returning the first value that it finds.
member.param: the "core" of the name by which the string is to be found
If not empty or null, used as a prefix to the key with an underscore delimiter.

Specifies whether to get the normal string (StringType.DisplayName) or the abbreviated or description versions of that string. The key is suffixed with "_A" for the abbreviated string and with "_D" for the description.

Specifies whether the returned string should be left in Title Case (this is how the strings should be written in the resource file) or converted to all lower case, or to sentence case (1st character only capitalized).
If true, attempts to get a localized string
member.returns: The string from the resource, or an empty string if none was found
